caption: Delicious food!
the place is so aesthetic, prices are affordable for the portion sizes, waiters are super nice, and the food is bussin’ 10/10 would def recommend :)

Don’t know why it has 4 stars it wasn’t a pleasant experience at all I’m from Detroit and have way better sushi my sushi rolls were falling apart and it’s just wasn’t good I also ordered the ramen noodles not good at all.. and when I told the waitress I didn’t like it she said next time don’t order if you don’t like🤨🥺 that’s not real hospitality also this list goes on they charge $15 in gratuity if you are visiting Chicago don’t eat there just my opinion

Still my favorite place to goto for sushi in the city. The portions are typically double of a standard restaurant and the food is always delicious.  The staff is nice too and the serving platters are cute!  Also the best place for Takoyaki in the city as well
Best Ramen Everrrrrrr

Great food, and I felt very safe with their Covid measures in place. My friend and I ate 3 maki rolls, and each had a different ramen bowl. Their bowls are huge and you can actually buy more noodles if you want! I'll definitly come back.

SO good! My husband and I have traveled the world, and have tried sushi everywhere. This place is really high on our list. We got the bagel, the flamer, and the sesame chicken. All so yummy. Absolute favorite was the flamer; very different, but warm goodness!

I was able to get a last minute reservation and be seated right away while arriving a few minutes early.  There was plenty of seating while they took proper covid precautions.  Every worker had a mask, and every table and chair was cleaned thoroughly between customers.  There was even a plastic shield between our table and the next. I will definitely be back!
Amazing food the service was amazing and the staff did an amazing job
Great place for Ramen, good vide to the Park  across the street
Great sushi selection plus many hot dishes to choose from.  Try the sake flight

Solid sushi for the price point! Everything was fresh and delicious. We got the shrimp tempura, the specialty tuna maki, and the mango tango sushi. Also tried the special hot and sour soup which was amazing! Would love to dine in once Covid restrictions are lifted

A gem among South Loop restaurants. The food is great quality for the price, and the atmosphere is lively enough to enjoy the presence of other people while still being quiet enough to hear those at your table. Always appreciated the service here, and highly recommend my favorite dish, the "Rock Shrimp."

Except for the fact that we had dinner outside freezing (due to COVID rules), is an excellent place! Service is good, food is great, flavor and size of the dishes are big enough for anybody. Please have a soup there!!!! Is delicious. Will come back if possible.
First timer at Niu B, trying Takoyaki for the first time as well.  You guys have made me a fan. Freaking loved it.
This place was so awesome, to be able to customize your Niu B was a plus and the staff was so helpful at explaining things off the menu defiantly will be back if I'm ever on the west coast again!
Food is not fresh. Not recommended
Spicy miso ramen was good but not spicy.
Went for lunch and had a great experience. The service was fast and friendly and the makis’ were fresh and well presented. The restaurant was clean and respected the covid safety measures.
Wonderful ramen and great service. They were very conscientious of covid and safe distancing.
Easily the best ramen I’ve ever had, probably the beat sushi too. I just love the depth if flavor in that spicy miso ramen.

In Chicago for 1 night, decided on Niu B instead of Chopsticks, and boy was that the best decision. Has a more authentic and relaxing vibe, staff are very helpful and courteous, and food was delicious. 10/10 would come again.
Food is SO good!! Huge portions! You will not walk away hungry!
The food was very delicious!

A really good COVID dining experience. We had several rolls, and they were all delicious and beautiful. All of the chefs and wait staff wore masks, and there were not too many people in the restaurant. Very nice dinner!
Food and atmosphere wow 🤩100/100. BUT look ain't everything. Ramen 🥰90/100 sashimi 10/100 :(. 😪😪🤒

One of my favorite sushi spots in the city! They never skimp on the rolls and the service is always kind and quick. The atmosphere is truly perfect for any occasion. During the COVID era, there is outdoor seating do you can get your people watching on right on Michigan Ave or inside with plenty of distance between you and other guests. Came with my partner to celebrate our 1 year anniversary as a couple and two years as best friends...We definitely made a great choice!

Visiting Chicago and I love my Sushi and this place happened to be very close to my hotel and I do not regret that walk .  Very friendly people that greet you with some ice water with a fresh slice of cucumber in it, so refreshing .  You must try the Cherry Blossom appetizer, it's just the most fresh tasting work of art I think I ever ate . It's a tuna tar tar topped with a beautiful bowl of avocado, just beautiful and the flavors just explode in your mouth . Will go back, maybe today !!! Oh and very decently priced.
I like this place a lot.   They have great food and good service

My fav spot for delicious Japanese food. I love visiting here. Looking forward to coming back with my relatives. The bill was fair for the quality of food. I can see why they have so many great reviews.

Everything was tasty and fresh: edamame, sushi, gyu-don and ramen and also a great take on an Old Fashioned. We are outside with comfortable social distancing and we were happy to see that the staff really were disinfecting tables between visitors. We'll be back.
Great scenery, average sushi. The staff was nice and welcoming. Stop in when you want a great view of Michigan Avenue, drinks, and a walk afterwards.

I meet friends in this lovely spot quite a bit! This is my favorite place to eat.  I visit this spot many times. The cooking is great, the staff members are courteous and the payment is affordable. I enjoy eating in this spot to have a good dinner.
Delicious sushi and awesome service!

Excellent!!! The price is perfect for what you pay for. The sushi just melts in your mouth 🤤

Delicious and affordable, with fantastic service and surprisingly good ... cocktails? Yes, cocktails. They make a surprisingly fantastic Suntori Toki old fashioned. My family and I went there for lunch, the food and service was wonderful!
Tokyo ramen was amazing. Chicken dumplings were good. Broth for ramen was rich and delicious. Pork belly was excellent. Very good. Will go again.
Great view, great food, this place made me like California sushi.

We came to this place for dinner. we heard about this place from a lot of people.  Well, we were not disappointed. The crew welcomed us with a smile and we felt good. The food was just great. We had a great time and we shall definitely come back again. We recommend this place to all.
Had a very good experience in this spot with my friend. The food came rapidly and the service is just good. Prices are convenient.

This restaurant is obviously one of the most attractive place in the area. Whenever I go there I am exceedingly pleased. They always keep their very high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they serve. You always win with this place. Very  recommended.

The Niu chain is one of my fav sushi spots. I used to frequent the one on Illinois until they built a more intimate one in the South Loop. My fav roll is the Rock n Roll and the Sexy Mexican, but you can't go wrong with anything you order. They also have a great cocktail menu and happy hour/lunch hour deals.

Dare I say this, but their sushi is just as good as the ones you can find in Japan!!! My husband and I were in Japan last year and we can definitely say this place is worth every penny. The customer service, the food, the taste, the experience. The fish is so fresh that it just melts in your mouth. I also loved how the soy sauce wasnt overly salty. For the water they also add a slice of cucumber which is a really nice touch. It's a must if you love Japanese cuisine!

Excellent food and fast service even though they were busy on a Saturday night. Could not pick a favorite, everything we had was very good.

Best sushi I’ve had in a while. The rice was light and perfect, the fish was nicely sliced and in perfect proportion to the rice. Delicious miso soup. They have a wonderful selection of awesome rolls. Can’t wait to come back as we were too full to have dessert.

The food and ambiance at this place are good but the service is mediocre. I ordered a fried tofu dish (yes, I love tofu!) but was disturbed to discover it was soft (not as appetizing) and not firm tofu. They should make this distinction on the menu; I would've gotten the vegetable tempura instead!

Food is pretty good, but service gives them 5 stars. Nokky was amazingly detailed in describing dishes, helpful in selecting them and attentive and observant throughout and after the meal. I watched her wipe my plate to ensure the presentation was perfect. And she suggested separate boxes for my leftovers, boxed them for me and boxes a container for the sauce without me requesting (maybe it’s the little things). Food wise, I had the rock shrimp, unagi nigiri and a dragon roll. The rock shrimp was deliciously seasoned and only lightly battered, as I prefer it. The dragon roll was delicious and massive. Sadly, I could only get to two pieces. Portions are relatively big for a Japanese place. I also had the sake flight, which was good quality and highly recommended. I’ll definitely be back.
Incredible!

I’m a regular here and I love this place! Hardly ever too crowded unless there’s something going on in town. Good food and good people work here! Very welcoming they know my order by heart!  Just today I forgot my chopsticks that are connected for easy eating and instead of getting me a fork they made me one with a rubber band and paper filling in between because they know that’s what I use.  I love this place and the people who work here.  Good sushi and ramen! Also the sesame chicken is another great dish!

Niu B Japanese Restaurant food was very good. I suggest that they heat the plate first before serving the dish of food. My chicken was a bit cool when I got it. My husband had to wait a few minutes before his dish was served. His salmon was served very hot. Atmosphere was very nice and especially liked the slice of cucumber in the glass of water! Nice touch!

The food was delicious! I can't wait to go back and try more on the menu. My next choice is the Ramen and the Honey Sesame Chicken yum!!!  Update: I got to try the Honey Sesame Chicken and it was yummy!!! My new favorite dish and I love broccoli so I'm glad I got the dish!

Stumbled upon Nui B randomly as I was walking in the neighborhood and decided to try it in the evening. When you walk in, the dark interiors and dim lighting make the place very inviting and open. I really enjoyed the food - we ordered wild mushroom soup which was delicious, vegetarian potstickers which were good too, and the four sushi we ordered were wonderful too. We ordered - zen sushi (not pictured), Rock n' roll, Spice Girl, Sexy Mexican. I honestly would give the this place a 4/5 but the service was not a pleasant experience. Our server was for some reason not welcoming and not attentive. We had ordered another sushi roll and waited for close to 20 mins for the order to come which never did despite her saying that it's ready. We had sent the Miso soup back because it was beyond salty and she was visibly not pleased. She was very pleasant with another set of table and didn't extend the same courtesy to us. It's a shame that the service was subpar because Nui B  has potential and I would love to visit again but will not be returning anytime soon.
Excellent food and service

Super delicious. Bad service. (Maybe it's a Chicago thing...) I ordered the Mellow Yellow and devoured it but our waiter didn't come back soon enough for me to order more food. I ended up leaving hungry.

My wife got the mellow yellow roll, which was good but she said she wanted an appetizer or another roll to be more filling. I got the tonkotsu which was AWESOME. I'm a pretty picky water but I liked the egg, pork, mushroom and whatever else was in it (I often don't). The broth was SO good I drank the whole dang thing. Tied with a joint in San Fran for best tonkotsu I've ever had. That said the waiter didn't realize we were there for about 4 minutes and then never came back until we were done, so my wife left hungry. So grab your waiter if you have to.

I would say that if you think Tabasco is too hot for you then don't even bother unless the chef can reduce the heat. Overall great experience and will definitely go back.

We also had an order of fried pork dumplings, which were tasty and very nicely prepared. I had the "bagel" roll, which has salmon, cream cheese, and avocado. It was also extremely tasty, perhaps the best I've had anywhere. The salmon was fresh and soft, not fishy at all. We had soup, appetizers, and main courses on the table as fast as we could eat them. Would absolutely come back.

First time ordering from them. Delivery 5 blocks away. Driver arrived over 75 min later and asked to me to meet him at the curb vs in my building lobby. Sushi was ok but nothing special. Maki rolls cheaply made with little fish. Won’t be ordering from them again—plenty of better options in the loop.

This place is great.  They're located in an awesome part of town.  The restaurant is clean and has a good atmosphere.  The service is just okay.  It's not bad and it's not great.  I didn't feel like removing a star just for average service because the food was so good.  Everyone at my table ordered a different kind of roll: 1 california rool, 1 spicy mexican roll, and 1 spice girl roll and all of them were delicious.  Even the california roll stood out for me as one of the best I've had.  They have a good diverse selection of drinks as well.
